cc.mallet.grmm.inference

Class JunctionTreePropagation

  • java.lang.Object
    • cc.mallet.grmm.inference.JunctionTreePropagation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

     class JunctionTreePropagation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    An implementation of Hugin-style propagation for junction trees. This destructively modifies the junction tree so that its clique potentials are the true marginals of the underlying graph.

    End users will not usually need to use this class directly. Use JunctionTreeInferencer instead.

    This class is not an instance of Inferencer because it destructively modifies the junction tree, which the Inferencer methods do not do to factor graphs.

    Created: Feb 1, 2006

    Version:
    $Id: JunctionTreePropagation.java,v 1.1 2007/10/22 21:37:49 mccallum Exp $
